t 38 (2000): 41-57[3] Piliero PJ "Interaction between ritonavir and statins." Am J Med 112 (2002): 510-1[4] "Product Information. Lexiva (fosamprenavir)." GlaxoSmithKline, Research Triangle Park, NC.[5] "Product Information. Norvir (ritonavir)." Abbott Pharmaceutical, Abbott Park, IL.[6] Cheng CH, Miller C, Lowe C, Pearson VE "Rhabdomyolysis due to probable interaction between simvastatin and ritonavir." Am J Health Syst Pharm 59 (2002): 728-30[7] "Product Information. Reyataz (atazanavir)." Bristol-Myers Squibb, Princeton, NJ.[8] Malaty LI, Kuper JJ "Drug interactions of HIV protease inhibitors." Drug Safety 20 (1999): 147-69[9] Neuvonen PJ, Backman JT, Niemi M "Pharmacokinetic comparison of the potential over-the-counter statins simvastatin, lovastatin, fluvastatin and pravastatin." Clin Pharmacokinet 47 (2008): 463-74[10] Fichtenbaum CJ, Gerber JG, Rosenkranz SL, et al. "Pharmacokinetic interactions between protease inhibitors and statins in HIV seronegative volunteers: ACTG Study A5047." AIDS 16 (2002): 569-577[11] "Product Information. Crixivan (indinavir)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.[12] Hare CB, Vu MP, Grunfeld C, Lampiris HW "Simvastatin-nelfinavir interaction implicated in rhabdomyolysis and death." Clin Infect Dis 35 (2002): E111-2[13] "Product Information. Prezista (darunavir)." Ortho Biotech Inc, Bridgewater, NJ.[14] "Product Information. Viracept (nelfinavir)." Agouron Pharma Inc, La Jolla, CA.[15] Schmidt GA, Hoehns JD, Purcell JL, Friedman RL, Elhawi Y "Severe rhabdomyolysis and acute renal failure secondary to concomitant use of simvastatin, amiodarone, and atazanavir." J Am Board Fam Med 20 (2007): 411-6[16] Mangum EM, Graham KK "Lopinavir-Ritonavir: a new protease inhibitor." Pharmacotherapy 21 (2001): 1352-63[17] Barry M, Mulcahy F, Merry C, Gibbons S, Back D "Pharmacokinetics and potential interactions amongst antiretroviral agents used to treat patients with HIV infection." Clin Pharmacokinet 36 (1999): 289-304[18] "Product Information. Agenerase (amprenavir)." Glaxo Wellcome, Research Triangle Pk, NC.[19] Richter WO, Jacob BG, Schwandt P "Interaction between fibre and lovastatin." Lancet 338 (1991): 706[20] Lilja JJ, Kivisto KT, Neuvonen PJ "Grapefruit juice-simvastatin interaction: Effect on serum concentrations of simvastatin, simvastatin acid, and HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors." Clin Pharmacol Ther 64 (1998): 477-83[21] Kantola T, Kivisto KT, Neuvonen PJ "Grapefruit juice greatly increases serum concentrations of lovastatin and lovastatin acid." Clin Pharmacol Ther 63 (1998): 397-402[22] "Product Information. Mevacor (lovastatin)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.[23] Bailey DG, Malcolm J, Arnold O, Spence JD "Grapefruit juice-drug interactions." Br J Clin Pharmacol 46 (1998): 101-10[24] Neuvonen PJ, Backman JT, Niemi M "Pharmacokinetic comparison of the potential over-the-counter statins simvastatin, lovastatin, fluvastatin and pravastatin." Clin Pharmacokinet 47 (2008): 463-74[25] Thompson PD, Clarkson P, Karas RH "Statin-associated myopathy." JAMA 289 (2003): 1681-90[26] "Product Information. Zocor (simvastatin)." Merck & Co, Inc, West Point, PA.[27] "Product Information. Prezista (darunavir)." Ortho Biotech Inc, Bridgewater, NJ.', 'Gemfibrozil, Fenofibric acid, Pitavastatin, Evinacumab, Evolocumab, Probucol, Dextrothyroxine, Cholestyramine, Ezetimibe, Clofibrate, Colestipol, More', 'Lamivudine, Paritaprevir, Tenofovir alafenamide, Maraviroc, Cabotegravir, Zanamivir, Rilpivirine, Dolutegravir, Brincidofovir, Elbasvir, Famciclovir, More', 1767369485);
